How to use GitHub with Atom
1 - Create a GitHub Account
2 - Create a Repository
3 - Copy .git link
4 - Paste it in Crtl+Shit+p GitHub:Clone
5 - Authorize GitHub for Atom on github.atom.io/login
6 - Copy token and paste it in github tab (bottom right)
7 - Make your code
8 - Go to git tab (up right)
9 - You can Stage All to push up every file or make one at a time (right click and stage)
10 - Write commit comment
11 - Then press create detached commit
12 - Create or select the branch where the commit is pushed
13 - Click on publish
14 - Fetch and pull to update the local Repository
